# Cursor Rules for portfolio-site (bobqiushao.online)

This project belongs to Bob Qiushao's bobqiushao-os.

## Before any changes
1. Read CLAUDE.md (this project's working agreement)
2. Read docs/00-charter/CHARTER.md (world view, 5 min)
3. Read relevant ADRs in docs/02-adr/

## Core prohibitions (from Charter + ADR)
- NEVER create product names wrapping Bob's capabilities (e.g., Auraloop X)
- NEVER limit the capability library to 4 types (it's open and expandable)
- NEVER redo existing assets (6 jewelry cases / Auraloop / Cursor workflow)
- NEVER speak directly to clients on Bob's behalf
- NEVER skip ADR / RUNBOOK / acceptance checklist before delivery

## Branch rules (ADR-0033)
- NEVER push directly to main
- Always use feature/*, fix/*, hotfix/*, or docs/* branches
- All merges must go through PR with description (what / why / how to test)

## Commit messages (Conventional Commits)
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- docs: documentation
- refactor: refactoring (no functional change)
- chore: build/tool changes

## i18n rule
All user-facing text changes MUST sync zh/en/ja in client/src/i18n/translations.ts

## Security
- NEVER write client credentials or API keys in code
- NEVER remove .env from .gitignore

## Performance baseline (ADR-0026)
- LCP < 2.5s
- CLS < 0.1
- Lighthouse Performance > 85

## CDN whitelist
Only load from: cdnjs.cloudflare.com, cdn.jsdelivr.net, fonts.googleapis.com, fonts.gstatic.com

## Animation rule
Always include prefers-reduced-motion protection in all animations.
